prhistory
Copyright 2013 Waitman Gobble
waitman@waitman.net

This program searches the GNATS database for PR corresponding to a port.

Command Switches:
-h I will show HELP
-l I will show legend
-u We will update PR db from the WWW
-c You will see closed PR TOO (AS WELL) if AVAILABLE
-p Display PR (ports only).

Run without search term and we will look for port in cwd.

Example:
# cd /usr/ports/lang/perl5.16
# prhistory

Example:
# prhistory perl

Example: lookup PR
# prhistory -p 123456

db file is stored in /var/db/ports/ports-pr.db (SQLite3)

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

Make options

make - build prhistory
make install - install prhistory to /usr/local/bin
make clean - clean src directory
make deinstall - remove prhistory from /usr/local/bin
make update - execute command `prhistory -u`

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

Create your own ports-pr.db
 see instructions at https://dx.burplex.com/bin/prhistory.html


